<center><h1>MULTIMEDIA INTERFACES--<BR>MULTIMEDIA CONTENT INDICATION</h1></center>
<hr>
</HEAD>
<BODY>

<H1>
I. Introduction</H1>

<H3>
Focus: issues and techniques of creating and using multimedia content indication
<BR>
-Not easy to design an effective multimedia interface that allows us
to make full use of multimedia
<BR>
-Past vs. Present
<BR>
-Need effective representations of multimedia contents
</H3>

<H1>
II. Issues</H1>

<H3>
-Multimedia Interface Cycle (<a href="c7fig/7-1.jpg">fig. 7.1</a>)
<BR><BR>
Issues in coping with the problems of the multimedia interface cycle:
<UL>
<LI>Interface design that realizes intuitive and effective interactions appropriate for the application and usage.  It should follow our information comprehensive style. This is the focus of this chapter.</LI>
<LI>Structure in data description and processing which realizes the above interface design with high flexibility and efficiency.</LI>
<LI>Processing algorithms that support the efficient data handling in computers.</LI>
</UL>
</H3>

<H1>
III. Related Work</H1>

<H3>
Research topics in interfaces for video handling:
<UL>
<LI>video content indication </LI>
<LI>video semantics representation</LI>
<LI>database visualization</LI>
</UL>

Examples:
<UL>
<LI>Video Streamer (<a href="c7fig/7-2.jpg">fig. 7-2</a>)</LI>
<LI>Video Browser (<a href="c7fig/7-3.jpg">fig. 7-3</a>)</LI>
<LI>Hierarchical Video Magnifier (<a href="c7fig/7-3.jpg">fig. 7-4</a>)</LI>
<LI>Media Streams</LI>
<LI>FilmFinder</LI>
</UL>
</H3>
